{{use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Use Australian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox language family | name = Maningrida | altname = Burarran | region = [[Northern Territory]] | familycolor = Australian | fam1 = [[Arnhem languages]] | glotto = mani1293 | glottoname = Maningrida | child1 = [[Guragone language|Guragone]] | child2 = [[Burarra language|Burarra]] | child3 = Ndjebbana | child4 = [[Nakkara language|Nakkara]] | map = Maningrida languages.png | mapcaption = Maningrida languages (purple), among other non-Pama-Nyungan languages (grey) }}
'''Maningrida''', also known as '''Burarran''', is a small family of [[Australian Aboriginal languages]] spoken in northern Australia. It includes four languages, none closely related: * [[Burarra language|Burarra]] * [[Guragone language|Gurr-goni]] * [[Djeebbana language|Ndjébbana]] * [[Nakkara language|Na'kara]]
Green established the family by reconstructing the [[tense–aspect–mood]] inflections of Proto-Maningrida, and demonstrated common developments that set them apart from other [[Arnhem languages]].{{sfn|Green|2003|pp=369–424}}{{sfn|Koch|2004|p=44}}
